---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { ArrowLeft } from '@lucide/astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Write Post">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] px-4 py-10">
    <a href="/" class="mb-5 inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-caption-bold text-pin-olive hover:text-pin-red">
      <ArrowLeft size={16} /> Back
    </a>
    <h1 id="page-heading" class="text-heading text-pin-plum">Write Post</h1>

    <form id="post-form" class="mt-6 flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div>
        <label class="mb-1.5 block text-caption-bold text-pin-olive">Title</label>
        <input name="title" required placeholder="Post title"
          class="w-full rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-[15px] py-[11px] text-body text-pin-plum outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pin-focus" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="mb-1.5 block text-caption-bold text-pin-olive">Tags (comma-separated)</label>
        <input name="tags" placeholder="e.g. postgres, indexing"
          class="w-full rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-[15px] py-[11px] text-body text-pin-plum outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pin-focus" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="mb-1.5 block text-caption-bold text-pin-olive">Date</label>
        <input name="date" type="date"
          class="w-full rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-[15px] py-[11px] text-body text-pin-plum outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pin-focus" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <label class="mb-1.5 block text-caption-bold text-pin-olive">Content</label>
        <p class="mb-2 text-caption text-pin-silver">Write freely, like Notion — headings, lists and quotes via Markdown shortcuts (#, -, &gt;), images by paste or drag &amp; drop. The first image becomes the card thumbnail. Drop a <code>.md</code> file anywhere on this page to import it.</p>
        <div id="editor"
          class="prose min-h-[420px] w-full max-w-none rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-6 py-5 text-pin-plum outline-none focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-pin-focus prose-headings:text-pin-plum prose-img:rounded-pin-sm [&_.ProseMirror]:min-h-[380px] [&_.ProseMirror]:outline-none"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2.5">
        <button id="submit-btn" type="submit" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-red px-5 py-2.5 text-caption-bold text-black hover:text-white">Save Post</button>
        <button id="download-btn" type="button" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-5 py-2.5 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">Download .md</button>
        <label class="cursor-pointer rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-5 py-2.5 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">
          Import .md
          <input id="md-file-input" type="file" accept=".md,text/markdown" class="hidden" />
        </label>
        <a href="/" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-5 py-2.5 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">Cancel</a>
      </div>
      <p id="save-error" class="hidden text-caption text-pin-error"></p>
    </form>

    <div id="publish-success" class="mt-5 hidden rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-5 py-4">
      <p class="text-caption-bold text-pin-plum">✅ 게시 완료! GitHub Pages 빌드 중 — 보통 1~3분 뒤 사이트에 반영됩니다.</p>
      <div class="mt-3 flex flex-wrap gap-2.5">
        <a href="/" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-4 py-2 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">홈으로</a>
        <a href="/new" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-4 py-2 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">새 글</a>
        <a id="view-commit-link" href="#" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-4 py-2 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">커밋 보기</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <details id="gh-settings" class="mt-5 rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-4 py-3">
      <summary class="cursor-pointer select-none text-caption-bold text-pin-plum">⚙️ GitHub 게시 설정</summary>
      <p class="mt-2 text-caption text-pin-olive">
        배포된 사이트에서 Save Post로 바로 게시하려면 Fine-grained 토큰(이 저장소만, Contents: Read and write)을
        저장하세요. 토큰은 이 브라우저의 localStorage에만 보관되며, GitHub API 호출 외에는 어디로도 전송되지 않습니다.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-2.5 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        <input id="gh-token-input" type="password" placeholder="github_pat_..." autocomplete="off"
          class="min-w-[240px] flex-1 rounded-pin border border-pin-silver bg-white px-[15px] py-[9px] text-caption text-pin-plum outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pin-focus" />
        <button type="button" id="gh-token-save" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-plum px-4 py-2 text-caption-bold text-white hover:bg-pin-red">저장</button>
        <button type="button" id="gh-token-clear" class="rounded-pin bg-pin-sand px-4 py-2 text-caption-bold text-pin-plum hover:text-pin-red">지우기</button>
      </div>
      <p id="gh-token-status" class="mt-2 text-caption text-pin-olive"></p>
    </details>

    <p id="help-text" class="mt-5 text-caption text-pin-olive">
      <strong>Save Post</strong> — 로컬(<code>npm run dev</code>)에서는 <code>/posts</code>에 파일을 쓰고 자동으로
      커밋·푸시한 뒤 홈으로 이동합니다. 배포된 사이트에서는 GitHub API로 저장소에 바로 커밋합니다(위 ⚙️ 설정에
      토큰 필요, 반영까지 1~3분). 실패하면 에러를 표시하니, <strong>Download .md</strong>로 파일을 직접 받아
      <code>/posts</code>에 넣을 수도 있습니다.
    </p>
  </section>

  <style is:global>
    .ProseMirror p.is-editor-empty:first-child::before {
      content: attr(data-placeholder);
      float: left;
      color: #91918c;
      pointer-events: none;
      height: 0;
    }
    .ProseMirror img[data-loading="true"] {
      background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #ecece6 0 12px, #f6f6f3 12px 24px);
      min-height: 160px;
    }
    .ProseMirror img[data-broken="true"] {
      background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #ecece6 0 12px, #f6f6f3 12px 24px);
      border: 1.5px dashed #bcbcb3;
      min-height: 140px;
      cursor: copy;
    }
  </style>

  <script type="module">
    import { Editor } from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/core@2.11.5';
    import StarterKit from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/starter-kit@2.11.5';
    import Image from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-image@2.11.5';
    import Link from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-link@2.11.5';
    import Table from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-table@2.11.5';
    import TableRow from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-table-row@2.11.5';
    import TableHeader from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-table-header@2.11.5';
    import TableCell from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-table-cell@2.11.5';
    import Placeholder from 'https://esm.sh/@tiptap/extension-placeholder@2.11.5';
    import TurndownService from 'https://esm.sh/turndown@7.2.0';
    import { gfm } from 'https://esm.sh/turndown-plugin-gfm@1.0.2';
    import { marked } from 'https://esm.sh/marked@12.0.2';

    // Track upload-in-flight images by a temporary id so we can find and
    // update the right ProseMirror node once the upload settles.
    const ImageWithUploadId = Image.extend({
      addAttributes() {
        return {
          ...this.parent?.(),
          'data-upload-id': { default: null },
        };
      },
    });

    const editor = new Editor({
      element: document.getElementById('editor'),
      extensions: [
        StarterKit,
        ImageWithUploadId,
        Link.configure({ openOnClick: false }),
        Table.configure({ resizable: false }),
        TableRow,
        TableHeader,
        TableCell,
        Placeholder.configure({ placeholder: 'Type here — # for heading, - for list, > for quote. Paste or drop images.' }),
      ],
    });

    const editorEl = document.getElementById('editor');

    // ---- Image upload, mimicking Notion: skeleton while uploading, never
    // a giant base64 blob in the saved markdown when a real upload works. ----

    function skeletonDataUri() {
      const svg = '<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="640" height="360">' +
        '<defs><pattern id="s" width="24" height="24" patternTransform="rotate(45)" patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse">' +
        '<rect width="12" height="24" fill="#ecece6"/><rect x="12" width="12" height="24" fill="#f6f6f3"/></pattern></defs>' +
        '<rect width="640" height="360" fill="url(#s)"/></svg>';
      return 'data:image/svg+xml;base64,' + btoa(svg);
    }

    async function uploadFile(file) {
      const form = new FormData();
      form.append('file', file);
      const res = await fetch('/api/upload', { method: 'POST', body: form });
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error('upload failed');
      const { url } = await res.json();
      return url;
    }

    function fileToDataUri(file) {
      return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
        const reader = new FileReader();
        reader.onload = () => resolve(String(reader.result));
        reader.onerror = reject;
        reader.readAsDataURL(file);
      });
    }

    function findImagePos(uploadId) {
      let pos = null;
      editor.state.doc.descendants((node, p) => {
        if (node.type.name === 'image' && node.attrs['data-upload-id'] === uploadId) pos = p;
      });
      return pos;
    }

    async function insertImageFile(file) {
      const uploadId = 'up-' + Date.now().toString(36) + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 7);
      editor.chain().focus().setImage({ src: skeletonDataUri(), alt: file.name, 'data-upload-id': uploadId }).run();
      // Mark the just-inserted <img> as loading for the skeleton stripe style.
      requestAnimationFrame(() => {
        const img = editorEl.querySelector('img[data-upload-id="' + uploadId + '"]');
        if (img) img.setAttribute('data-loading', 'true');
      });

      let finalSrc;
      try {
        finalSrc = await uploadFile(file);
      } catch {
        // No upload server available (e.g. static GitHub Pages deploy) —
        // fall back to embedding the image directly so no work is lost.
        finalSrc = await fileToDataUri(file);
      }

      const pos = findImagePos(uploadId);
      if (pos != null) {
        const node = editor.state.doc.nodeAt(pos);
        editor.view.dispatch(
          editor.state.tr.setNodeMarkup(pos, undefined, { ...node.attrs, src: finalSrc })
        );
      }
    }

    editorEl.addEventListener('paste', (e) => {
      const items = e.clipboardData && e.clipboardData.items;
      if (!items) return;
      for (const it of items) {
        if (it.type.indexOf('image') === 0) {
          e.preventDefault();
          insertImageFile(it.getAsFile());
        }
      }
    });
    editorEl.addEventListener('dragover', (e) => e.preventDefault());
    editorEl.addEventListener('drop', (e) => {
      // Dropping onto a broken image replaces just that image (Notion-style).
      if (e.target instanceof HTMLImageElement && e.target.dataset.broken === 'true') {
        const files = e.dataTransfer && e.dataTransfer.files;
        const file = files && files[0];
        if (file && file.type.indexOf('image') === 0) {
          e.preventDefault();
          e.stopPropagation();
          replaceBrokenImage(e.target, file);
        }
        return;
      }
      const files = e.dataTransfer && e.dataTransfer.files;
      if (!files || files.length === 0) return;
      e.preventDefault();
      e.stopPropagation();
      const mdFile = Array.from(files).find(isMarkdownFile);
      if (mdFile) {
        importMarkdownFile(mdFile);
        return;
      }
      for (const f of files) {
        if (f.type.indexOf('image') === 0) insertImageFile(f);
      }
    });

    // ---- Broken images (e.g. after importing a .md with a local path that
    // doesn't exist here) — flag them and let the user drop a replacement. ----
    async function replaceBrokenImage(imgEl, file) {
      imgEl.removeAttribute('data-broken');
      imgEl.setAttribute('data-loading', 'true');
      let finalSrc;
      try {
        finalSrc = await uploadFile(file);
      } catch {
        finalSrc = await fileToDataUri(file);
      }
      let pos = null;
      editor.state.doc.descendants((node, p) => {
        if (node.type.name === 'image' && editor.view.nodeDOM(p) === imgEl) pos = p;
      });
      if (pos != null) {
        const node = editor.state.doc.nodeAt(pos);
        editor.view.dispatch(editor.state.tr.setNodeMarkup(pos, undefined, { ...node.attrs, src: finalSrc }));
      } else {
        imgEl.src = finalSrc;
      }
    }

    editorEl.addEventListener(
      'error',
      (e) => {
        const img = e.target;
        if (img instanceof HTMLImageElement && img.dataset.broken !== 'true' && !img.src.startsWith('data:image/svg+xml')) {
          img.dataset.broken = 'true';
          img.alt = 'Image not found — drop a new image here to replace it';
          img.title = img.alt;
        }
      },
      true
    );

    // Keep in sync with src/lib/posts.ts's slugify — must support Korean
    // titles (À-ɏ covers accented Latin, 가-힣 covers Hangul syllables) or a
    // Korean-only title collapses to an empty/mangled slug.
    function slugify(v) {
      return v.toLowerCase().trim().replace(/[^a-z0-9À-ɏ가-힣]+/g, '-').replace(/(^-|-$)/g, '');
    }

    // ---- Edit an existing post: prefill from /posts/<slug>.json ----
    const editSlug = new URLSearchParams(location.search).get('edit');
    const form = document.getElementById('post-form');
    const submitBtn = document.getElementById('submit-btn');
    let editingSlug = null;

    // Full CommonMark + GFM parsing (lists, blockquotes, links, tables, ...)
    // via marked, instead of a hand-rolled subset.
    function markdownToHtml(body) {
      return body && body.trim() ? marked.parse(body) : '<p></p>';
    }

    function isMarkdownFile(file) {
      return file && (file.name.toLowerCase().endsWith('.md') || file.type === 'text/markdown');
    }

    // ---- Parse "---\nkey: value\n---" frontmatter, tolerating both inline
    // arrays (tags: ["a", "b"]) and YAML block-list arrays. ----
    function parseFrontmatter(text) {
      const m = text.match(/^---\r?\n([\s\S]*?)\r?\n---\r?\n?([\s\S]*)$/);
      if (!m) return { meta: {}, body: text };
      const [, yaml, rest] = m;
      const meta = {};
      const lines = yaml.split(/\r?\n/);
      for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
        const kv = lines[i].match(/^(\w+):\s*(.*)$/);
        if (!kv) continue;
        const key = kv[1];
        const val = kv[2].trim();
        if (val === '' && lines[i + 1] && /^\s*-\s+/.test(lines[i + 1])) {
          const items = [];
          while (lines[i + 1] && /^\s*-\s+/.test(lines[i + 1])) {
            i++;
            items.push(lines[i].replace(/^\s*-\s+/, '').trim().replace(/^["']|["']$/g, ''));
          }
          meta[key] = items;
        } else if (/^\[.*\]$/.test(val)) {
          meta[key] = val.slice(1, -1).split(',').map((s) => s.trim().replace(/^["']|["']$/g, '')).filter(Boolean);
        } else {
          meta[key] = val.replace(/^["']|["']$/g, '');
        }
      }
      return { meta, body: rest.replace(/^\n+/, '') };
    }

    async function importMarkdownFile(file) {
      const text = await file.text();
      const { meta, body } = parseFrontmatter(text);
      let title = meta.title;
      let content = body;
      if (!title) {
        const h1 = content.match(/^#\s+(.+)$/m);
        if (h1) { title = h1[1].trim(); content = content.replace(h1[0], '').trim(); }
      }
      if (title) form.title.value = title;
      if (meta.tags) form.tags.value = (Array.isArray(meta.tags) ? meta.tags : [meta.tags]).join(', ');
      if (meta.date) form.date.value = meta.date;
      editor.commands.setContent(markdownToHtml(content));
    }

    const mdFileInput = document.getElementById('md-file-input');
    mdFileInput.addEventListener('change', (e) => {
      const file = e.target.files && e.target.files[0];
      if (file) importMarkdownFile(file);
      e.target.value = '';
    });

    // Drop a .md file anywhere on the page (outside the editor) to import it.
    document.addEventListener('dragover', (e) => e.preventDefault());
    document.addEventListener('drop', (e) => {
      if (editorEl.contains(e.target)) return;
      const files = e.dataTransfer && e.dataTransfer.files;
      const file = files && files[0];
      if (file && isMarkdownFile(file)) {
        e.preventDefault();
        importMarkdownFile(file);
      }
    });

    if (editSlug) {
      fetch('/posts/' + encodeURIComponent(editSlug) + '.json')
        .then((r) => (r.ok ? r.json() : null))
        .then((data) => {
          if (!data) return;
          editingSlug = data.slug;
          document.getElementById('page-heading').textContent = 'Edit Post';
          submitBtn.textContent = 'Save changes';
          document.getElementById('help-text').innerHTML =
            'Save changes를 누르면 <code>posts/' + data.slug + '.md</code>가 같은 파일명으로 저장·커밋됩니다.';
          form.title.value = data.title || '';
          form.tags.value = (data.tags || []).join(', ');
          form.date.value = data.date || '';
          editor.commands.setContent(markdownToHtml(data.body || ''));
        })
        .catch(() => {});
    }

    // Build the frontmatter + markdown string from the current form/editor
    // state. Shared by the Save (local write) and Download (.md file) actions
    // so they always produce identical output. Returns null if title is empty.
    function buildMarkdown() {
      const title = form.title.value.trim();
      if (!title) return null;
      const tags = form.tags.value.split(',').map((t) => t.trim()).filter(Boolean);
      const date = form.date.value.trim() || new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);

      const html = editor.getHTML();
      const parsed = new DOMParser().parseFromString(html, 'text/html');
      const firstImg = parsed.querySelector('img');
      const thumbnail = firstImg ? firstImg.getAttribute('src') : '';

      // Tiptap's table HTML (colspan/rowspan="1", <p> inside every cell) makes
      // turndown-plugin-gfm bail out to a raw <table> passthrough — flatten it
      // first so tables export as real markdown pipe tables.
      parsed.querySelectorAll('td, th').forEach((cell) => {
        cell.removeAttribute('colspan');
        cell.removeAttribute('rowspan');
        const paragraphs = cell.querySelectorAll('p');
        if (paragraphs.length) cell.innerHTML = Array.from(paragraphs).map((p) => p.innerHTML).join('<br>');
      });
      parsed.querySelectorAll('table').forEach((t) => {
        t.removeAttribute('style');
        t.querySelectorAll('colgroup').forEach((cg) => cg.remove());
      });

      const td = new TurndownService({ headingStyle: 'atx', codeBlockStyle: 'fenced' });
      td.use(gfm);
      const markdown = td.turndown(parsed.body.innerHTML);

      const content = '---\n' +
        'title: "' + title.replace(/"/g, '\\"') + '"\n' +
        'date: ' + date + '\n' +
        'tags: [' + tags.map((t) => '"' + t.replace(/"/g, '\\"') + '"').join(', ') + ']\n' +
        (thumbnail ? 'thumbnail: "' + thumbnail + '"\n' : '') +
        '---\n\n' + markdown + '\n';

      const slug = editingSlug || slugify(title);
      return { slug, content };
    }

    function downloadMarkdown({ slug, content }) {
      const blob = new Blob([content], { type: 'text/markdown' });
      const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
      const a = document.createElement('a');
      a.href = url;
      a.download = slug + '.md';
      document.body.appendChild(a);
      a.click();
      a.remove();
      URL.revokeObjectURL(url);
    }

    const saveError = document.getElementById('save-error');
    const successPanel = document.getElementById('publish-success');
    const commitLink = document.getElementById('view-commit-link');

    // ---- GitHub publishing (deployed static site) ----
    // There is no /api/save server on GitHub Pages, so on the live site
    // Save Post commits posts/<slug>.md straight to the repo via the GitHub
    // Contents API, authenticated with a fine-grained PAT the user stores in
    // localStorage below. The token never appears in source — input only.
    const GH_OWNER = 'Mm-767';
    const GH_REPO = 'Mm-767.github.io';
    const GH_BRANCH = 'main';
    const IS_LOCAL = location.hostname === 'localhost' || location.hostname === '127.0.0.1';

    const tokenInput = document.getElementById('gh-token-input');
    const tokenStatus = document.getElementById('gh-token-status');
    function refreshTokenStatus() {
      const t = localStorage.getItem('gh_pat');
      tokenStatus.textContent = t
        ? '토큰 저장됨 (…' + t.slice(-4) + ') — 이 브라우저에서만 사용됩니다.'
        : '저장된 토큰 없음.';
    }
    refreshTokenStatus();
    document.getElementById('gh-token-save').addEventListener('click', () => {
      const v = tokenInput.value.trim();
      if (!v) { tokenInput.focus(); return; }
      localStorage.setItem('gh_pat', v);
      tokenInput.value = '';
      refreshTokenStatus();
    });
    document.getElementById('gh-token-clear').addEventListener('click', () => {
      localStorage.removeItem('gh_pat');
      refreshTokenStatus();
    });

    // UTF-8-safe base64 — plain btoa() throws on Korean text, and huge data:
    // URIs need chunking to avoid call-stack limits in String.fromCharCode.
    function utf8ToBase64(str) {
      const bytes = new TextEncoder().encode(str);
      let bin = '';
      for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i += 0x8000) {
        bin += String.fromCharCode.apply(null, bytes.subarray(i, i + 0x8000));
      }
      return btoa(bin);
    }

    function ghHeaders(token) {
      return {
        Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token,
        Accept: 'application/vnd.github+json',
        'X-GitHub-Api-Version': '2022-11-28',
      };
    }

    function ghErrorMessage(status, stage) {
      if (status === 401) return 'GitHub 토큰이 유효하지 않습니다(만료·철회) — ⚙️ GitHub 게시 설정에서 새 토큰을 저장하세요.';
      if (status === 403) return 'GitHub이 요청을 거부했습니다(403) — 토큰에 이 저장소의 Contents: Read and write 권한이 있는지 확인하세요.';
      if (status === 404) return '저장소에 접근할 수 없습니다(404) — 토큰의 저장소 선택에 ' + GH_OWNER + '/' + GH_REPO + '가 포함돼 있는지 확인하세요.';
      return 'GitHub API 오류 (HTTP ' + status + ', ' + stage + ') — 잠시 후 다시 시도해 보세요.';
    }

    async function publishToGitHub({ slug, content }, title, token) {
      // Encode each path segment, never the slashes between them.
      const encPath = ['posts', slug + '.md'].map(encodeURIComponent).join('/');
      const url = 'https://api.github.com/repos/' + GH_OWNER + '/' + GH_REPO + '/contents/' + encPath;

      // Updating an existing file requires its current sha; 404 = new file.
      let sha = null;
      const lookup = await fetch(url + '?ref=' + GH_BRANCH, { headers: ghHeaders(token) });
      if (lookup.ok) {
        sha = (await lookup.json()).sha || null;
      } else if (lookup.status !== 404) {
        throw new Error(ghErrorMessage(lookup.status, 'sha 조회'));
      }

      const body = {
        message: (sha ? 'Update post: ' : 'Add post: ') + title,
        content: utf8ToBase64(content),
        branch: GH_BRANCH,
      };
      if (sha) body.sha = sha;

      const put = await fetch(url, {
        method: 'PUT',
        headers: { ...ghHeaders(token), 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify(body),
      });
      if (!put.ok) throw new Error(ghErrorMessage(put.status, '커밋'));
      const data = await put.json();
      return { commitUrl: (data.commit && data.commit.html_url) || 'https://github.com/' + GH_OWNER + '/' + GH_REPO + '/commits/' + GH_BRANCH };
    }

    // Save Post — two paths:
    //  * localhost: the dev server's /api/save writes into /posts, commits,
    //    pushes in the background, and we go home to see the post.
    //  * live site: commit via the GitHub Contents API and show the success
    //    panel instead of redirecting (the static rebuild takes a few minutes,
    //    so the post wouldn't be on the home page yet).
    form.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault();
      saveError.classList.add('hidden');
      successPanel.classList.add('hidden');
      const built = buildMarkdown();
      if (!built) { form.title.focus(); return; }

      submitBtn.disabled = true;
      const originalLabel = submitBtn.textContent;
      submitBtn.textContent = 'Saving…';
      try {
        if (IS_LOCAL) {
          const res = await fetch('/api/save', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
            body: JSON.stringify(built),
          });
          if (!res.ok) throw new Error('Save endpoint returned ' + res.status);
          const data = await res.json();
          if (data.gitError) {
            // Saved to /posts locally, but the automatic commit failed (no git
            // identity configured, no repo, ...) — stay on the page and say so
            // instead of redirecting as if it published. (The push itself runs
            // in the background; its failures are logged to the dev terminal.)
            saveError.textContent =
              'Saved locally (posts/' + built.slug + '.md) but the automatic git commit failed: ' + data.gitError +
              ' — run git add/commit/push yourself to publish it.';
            saveError.classList.remove('hidden');
            return;
          }
          location.href = '/';
          return;
        }

        const token = localStorage.getItem('gh_pat');
        if (!token) {
          document.getElementById('gh-settings').open = true;
          throw new Error('게시하려면 GitHub 토큰이 필요합니다 — 아래 ⚙️ GitHub 게시 설정에 토큰을 저장한 뒤 다시 Save Post를 누르세요.');
        }
        const { commitUrl } = await publishToGitHub(built, form.title.value.trim(), token);
        commitLink.href = commitUrl;
        successPanel.classList.remove('hidden');
        successPanel.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });
        return;
      } catch (err) {
        saveError.textContent = IS_LOCAL
          ? 'Could not save to /posts — make sure "npm run dev" is running in a terminal (restart it if you just pulled these changes). ' +
            'Use "Download .md" to save the file yourself instead.'
          : (err && err.message) || '게시에 실패했습니다.';
        saveError.classList.remove('hidden');
      } finally {
        submitBtn.disabled = false;
        submitBtn.textContent = originalLabel;
      }
    });

    document.getElementById('download-btn').addEventListener('click', () => {
      const built = buildMarkdown();
      if (!built) { form.title.focus(); return; }
      downloadMarkdown(built);
    });
  </script>
</BaseLayout>
